task.summary: Minor GUI update fixed dailymealadapter not displaying correct weight_amount because multiplier was not functioning correctly fixed dailymealadapter not displaying correct macros when using multiplier other than 1 fixed main activity not making the correct macro adjustments when a dailymeal with a multiplier other than 1 is in the list
Fixed DailyMealAdapter deleting and inserting display bugs
Finished implementing ViewSavedMealActivity, Edit and Delete functionality is now working! Ez last push boys
Added Progress Bar Library Added 3 Progress Bars in home activity
Added labels on progress bars Removed old labels (goal, left)
Added labels to progress bars Removed old labels (Goals, left)
Made progress bar labels align to the right

----1---- Changed Carb/Protein/Fat in meals from int to float. Carb/Protein/Fat in user have remain unchanged. The total C/P/F for a meal are the base_macro * multiplier but rounded to the nearest int. Example: Before adding the Meal: Daily macros consumed where 10c, 20p, 10f Created a new Meal = Chicken, 0.0c, 33.3p, 4.7f, 100g Added the same Meal but with different amount = 45g, => multiplier = 45/100 = 0.45 Daily Meal entry = Chicken 0.0c, 33.3*0.45 = 14.985p => rounded to 15p, 4.7f*0.45 = 2.115 => rounded to 2f After adding the Meal: Daily macros consumed become 10+0 = 0c, 20 + 15 = 35p, 10 +2 = 12f ----2---- Changed serving from int to float. Made all neccessary GUI changes in order to make app functional (still need to revisit, re-evaluate and optimize them).
Tested the previous changes and fixed the bugs.
Fixed sorting meals by name (ascending) in ViewSavedMealsActivity Changed amount - > quantity across entire project
Added functional search bar in ViewSavedMealActivity and SelectSavedMealActivity
